  "prompt": "What does \u201csocially inept\u201d mean?",
  "response": "\"Socially inept\" refers to someone who lacks the skills or confidence to interact effectively in social situations. This can manifest as difficulty in understanding social cues, making conversation, or engaging appropriately with others. Such individuals may struggle with forming relationships or fitting into social norms, which can lead to awkwardness or misunderstandings. Being socially inept is not necessarily a reflection of a person's intelligence or value; rather, it highlights challenges in navigating social interactions.",
